<TEXT>
hordes of cropdevouring locusts 
sweeping across northwestern africa have reached mali and the 
government has issued an urgent plea for foreign help 
mali agriculture minister moulaye mohamed has asked for 
140000 52000 gallons of insecticide and 500 hours of airplane 
time to launch a spraying campaign according to mali radio 
it is while going through hard times that one knows ones true 
friends moulaye told the diplomatic corps in the capital of 
bamako on thursday according to the broadcast 
it said he called the locusts a major threat moving south 
from algeria and mauritania and advancing as far as 160 acres a day 
he said the first swarms in mali were reported monday near the 
western city of kayes 
the intensity of the swarm was estimated at more than 200 
insects per square yard the minister said and they were 
destroying up to 40 percent of vegetation 
locust invasions have been a seasonal occurence in many parts of 
africa for hundreds of years but the romebased un food and 
agricultural organization has called the present crisis the worst 
in 30 years 
</TEXT>
