<TEXT>
a postcard mailed from the titanic fetched 2068 
during an auction friday the 76th anniversary of the ocean liners 
sinking but a waterstained letter found on the body of a dead 
passenger went unsold 
the auction of 200 items of titanic memorabilia raised 56400 
onslows auctioneers reported 
a spokesman said the waterstained letter didnt sell because it 
may have been considered too ghoulish 
one collector paid 2068 for the postcard stamped on the ship 
and posted when it stopped in ireland 
northern irelands ulster folk and transport museum paid the 
auctions top price of 14100 for a 1912 watercolor painting 
entitled fitting out the titanic belfast 
the titanic built in belfast northern ireland and declared 
unsinkable went down in the atlantic on april 15 1912 after 
hitting an iceberg while on its maiden voyage from southampton 
england to new york a total of 1513 people perished 
the wreck of the liner about 25 miles below the surface and 350 
miles south of newfoundland was first located by a usfrench 
expedition in september 1985 
