<TEXT>
khalil alwazir a bakers son who built 
a guerrilla army from what began as a secret student cell fought 
the war against israel for 35 years and was the heirapparent of 
plo chairman yasser arafat 
alwazir known throughout the middle east by his nomdeguerre 
abu jihad father of the holy war was slain early saturday at his 
home in tunis 
he was known in the plo as the revolutions honest man he 
rarely wore a uniform unlike arafat and listened more than he 
spoke 
bodyguards called him the wailing wall and complained that 
scores of people were allowed to visit him every day to tell their 
troubles and seek his help 
the palestine liberation organizations military commander was 
born in ramle in what was palestine on oct 10 1935 
in 1948 when he was 13 his family moved to gaza after israel 
was created he became leader of the students union in high school 
and formed a clandestine cell that challenged egypts rule over the 
gaza strip 
egyptian authorities arrested alwazir in 1954 and held him for 
several weeks he led his first major guerrilla operation the next 
year blowing up water tanks near beit hanoun 
during the 1956 middle east war alwazir went to egypt and 
enrolled in the alexandria university law school 
while in egypt he met two other students yasser arafat and 
salah khalaf they founded fatah an underground group dedicated to 
regaining the land palestinians lost to israeli 
fatah a reverse acronym in arabic for the palestine national 
liberation movement was to become the core of the palestinian 
movement 
arafat graduated with a civil engineering degree within a year 
and got a job in kuwaits public works ministry alwazir dropped 
out went to saudi arabia seeking work and in 1962 married his 
cousin intisar 
alwazir khalaf and arafat reunited in kuwait and began 
recruiting for their movement alwazir moved to algiers in 1963 to 
found asifa arabic for storm and persuaded the algerians to help 
train about 100 young palestinian fighters 
he and arafat went to china seeking help for fatah arafat soon 
returned to kuwait but alwazir stayed in asia for several months 
training in north korea china and north vietnam 
returning to the middle east he established military 
headquarters in damascus syria 
on jan 1 1965 alwazir made a raid into israel from syrias 
golan heights and claimed responsibility for fatah because of 
that jan 1 has become revolution day for the 5 million 
palestinians 
the syrians arrested alwazir and several fatah members in may 
1966 he was freed after 45 days 
arafat shuttled among arab capitals seeking political 
recognition and financial support for fatah alwazir recruited and 
trained young arab fighters and conducted more military operations 
into israel from syria and lebanon 
in 1967 he led asifa infiltrators into israels north his men 
fought the jordanian army in 1970 when king hussein drove the 
guerrillas from jordan 
after the 1970 black september fighting in jordan the plo 
set up headquarters in lebanon three years later alwazir was 
named deputy commander of the plo and led palestinian units who 
fought the israelis in the 1973 middle east war 
over the next nine years he concentrated on guerrilla raids 
into israel forming infiltration units and establishing 
underground cells in the iseraelioccupied west bank and gaza strip 
israel invaded lebanon in 1982 the plo left and alwazir 
resumed his base in damascus relations with the syrians collapsed 
in 1983 and alwazir moved to tripoli in north lebanon but 
syrianbacked militiamen drove the plo out of the city in december 
1983 
alwazir retained the respect of dissident plo elements and 
syrian leaders and made several futile attempts to reconcile arafat 
and president hafez assad of syria whose personal feud had 
undermined the syrianplo alliance 
he moved to jordan in 1984 but was expelled in july 1986 after 
hussein terminated an agreement with arafat he then moved to 
tunis where the plo now has its headquarters 
survivors are his widow also known as umm jihad mother of the 
holy war sons jihad 24 bassem 21 and nidal 2 and daughters 
iman 18 and hanan 14 
</TEXT>
