rekindled fears that the iranians were again mining shipping lanes 
in the strategic waterway after laying off for several months 
following clashes with us forces 
associated press reporter richard pyle aboard the uss 
wainwright in the gulf reported that navy divers saturday 
detonated two mines in the central gulf near where the roberts was 
hit mine sweepers and helicopters searched for others 
the roberts was the first us navy ship damaged in the gulf 
since an iraqi warplane attacked the frigate stark with missiles 
may 17 1987 killing 37 crewmen the iraqis said the pilot mistook 
the stark for an iranian warship 
the us navy supported by warships from several western 
european countries increased its presence in the gulf last july to 
protect reflagged kuwaiti tankers from iranian attack 
the kuwait vessels were reregistered in the united states so 
they could fly the us flag iran accuses kuwait of aiding iraqs 
war effort 
