texas air corp said vance but he added that with the court 
decision on the shuttle concern grew and grew 
an internal department alert memo was prepared noting texas 
airs record losses of 466 million in 1987 and its debts of more 
than 5 billion requiring 600 million in interest payments 
new filings meanwhile by texas air with the securities and 
exchange commission raised additional red flags vance and 
scocozza noted the sec filings provided more details on a series 
of bothersome transactions between texas air and eastern that 
suggested assets were being drained from eastern 
texas air had moved easterns valuable computer reservation 
